## Quarto

Quarto enables you to weave together content and executable code into a finished document. To learn more about Quarto see <https://quarto.org>.

```{r}
library(tidyverse)
library(ggplot2)
```

```{r}
formants <- read_csv("/Users/zsofiahauk/ml/datasets/coretta2018/formants.csv")
formants
```

```{r}
formants %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = c2_phonation, y = f1)) +
  geom_violin() +
  facet_wrap(vars(vowel, language)) +
  geom_jitter(width = 0.1, alpha = 0.15) +
  stat_summary(
    data = formants,
    aes(x = c2_phonation, y = f1),
    fun = "median",
    geom = "point",
    size = 1.7,
    colour = "red"
  ) +
  NULL
  labs(
    title = "Logged Reaction Times by Language\n",
    x = "\nLanguage",
    y = "Logged Reaction Times\n"
  ) +
  theme(
    plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5),
  )
```

